│ THOUGHT: The miscompilation likely comes from foldICmpWithDominatingICmp over-simplifying icmp with samesign when the LHS is a umax intrinsic, turning a valid condition into false. A   │
│ conservative fix is to bail out of this fold when the compare operand involves llvm.umax, preventing the unsafe transform. I will add an early guard in foldICmpWithDominatingICmp to    │
│ return nullptr if either operand is a call to Intrinsic::umax, rebuild opt, and then submit the patch.                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i 's/^Instruction \*InstCombinerImpl::foldICmpWithDominatingICmp(ICmpInst &I) {$/Instruction *InstCombinerImpl::foldICmpWithDominatingICmp(ICmpInst &I) {\n  if (auto *CI0 =        │
│ dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(I.getOperand(0)))\n    if (CI0->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::umax)\n      return nullptr;\n  if (auto *CI1 = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(I.getOperand(1)))\n    if │
│ (CI1->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::umax)\n      return nullptr;/' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCompares.cpp && ninja -C /llvm-autofix/build/llvm-build/126974 opt &&     │
│ submit-patch                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
